1 I ordered the kingdom plate i think it's called for $25.   it came with 2 small kofta kebabs (which were made from lamb instead of lean beef as the menu stated, 2 small cubes of tasteless meat, 2 small cubes of chicken.  it also came with a salad and veggies.  the entire meal should have cost no more than $7.     needless to say i will not be visiting that establishment anytime soon.
4 After calling to check that this restaraunt does deliver (which they do as long as your order is at least $30) we decided to give them a try.  We are big fans of greek food and the traditional fare with the kabob flair looked to be pretty enticing.  Honestly, I was not expecting this place to blow me away.  The portions were small compared to other restaraunts and this is the only thing keeping me from giving it 5 stars.  For a dinner that I would have rather paid $35 for, I paid almost $50, but I have to admit, the food was totally worth it.  We ordered the hummus trio with extra pita bread and the kabob dinner for 2.  I have been to quite a few Greek restaraunts in my time and none of them have left me saying Wow.  I'm still tasting the yummy spices.  The meats were flavorful, the rice was delicious, the hummus was fresh and each had it's own unique flavor and even the vegetables were delectable.  I don't know what spices they are using, but it was amazing.  Even the dinner salad that came with the meal was fresh and tasty.  I most defintiely will be dining here again soon, whenever I get the yen for a tasty meat and rice dish served up with some hot pita bread and I suggest you do the same.
5 This place is awesome!! My girlfriend and I went here for the first time this afternoon for lunch.  They gave us a small sample platter of four different types of humus and toasted pitas on the house.   They were all good, but the artichoke was our favorite.   We both ordered the Gyro with a side salad for our meal.  We came a little late so we were the only people there.  Service was very quick.  Both the salad and the Gyro were fantastic!  The gyro is probably one of the best I've ever had!  The meat was VERY tender and had an amazing flavor... seasoned perfectly! We will definitely be back for more!! We even ordered a large order of the humus to go.
4 Ate at the Nile Cafe last night. It's a medium sized restaurant in a strip mall. Sparse decor with a couple of TVs. VERY family friendly, as the proprietor had his kid there.   The best part about the place was the kind, attentive service. Our pretty waitress and the owner both thanked us a couple of times for stopping in. They just seemed really grateful.  As other reviewers noted, the small sampler plate of hummus was a nice free starter. I had the salad with my dinner. It was a basic plate of lettuce (with a decent dressing). I recommend the lentil soup, instead.  I had the gyro schwarama, which came with a generous portion of rice. It was enough to have left overs for lunch today, but it was all a bit greasy (though, in their defense, greek is almost always a bit greasy). Tender, flavorful meat.  The highligh of the meal was the caring servers.
